
In order to validate a program P, we must first recursively validate all
dependencies of P.

For simplicity, at the moment, we assume the hardware on which the validation
takes place is correct (not a good assumption to make, but we have to start
somewhere).

Itself!
Programming Language (L)
  Language compiler/interpreter (C)
    Libraries on which compiler depends
      Operating system (OS) on which C runs
    shell in which C runs
      
